#week-title("One", "Nitrum & Salt: The Polar Tension")

=== Core Teaching

The *Golden Chain of Homer* reveals that all creation proceeds from the dynamic
tension between two fundamental principles: the *Volatile* (called *Nitrum*
or the universal acid) and the *Fixed* (called *Salt* or the universal alkali).

These two are not opposites in conflict; they are complementaries in an eternal
embrace. The volatile descends as rain and dew, carrying the living creative
force. The fixed salt of the earth acts as a magnet, attracting and holding this
volatile force.

#doctrine[
  _"The volatile of rain is gradually fixed into salt by the earth's warmth; the
  fixed salt is dissolved and re-volatilized by fresh rain. And so the cycle
  continues without end."_
  #align(right)[— _Golden Chain of Homer_, Part II]
]

=== Topics This Week

- Nitrum: The universal creative acid and its movements
- The fixed alkali: The universal magnet of the earth
- The eternal cycle of fixing the volatile and volatilizing the fixed

#inner-work[
  *The Descending Flash*

  Meditate on the image of the "descending lightning flash" from the Qabalah.
  Imagine the volatile force of the heavens descending into your own physical
  body (the Malkuth).

  How does your body "magnetise" or "fix" your inspirations? Record your
  reflections in your journal.
]

